  "title": "X018 calibration baseline \u2014 cartograph commission, no surface map",
  "body": "Pre-flight calibration trial for X018. Replays the cartograph commission\n(writ w-mojmj0rc, originally produced spec session ses-mojmj4zc-e81d52ed\nat $8.08, 14.6 min) under the lab.plan-only rig with NO surface map\ninjection. Purpose: validate the lab.plan-only recipe end-to-end and\nmeasure apparatus fidelity vs the real-world session.\n\nThe reader-analyst's cost (USD) and tool-call profile from this trial\nis compared against $8.08 to decide which reference baseline X018\nvariant trials use:\n\n- Within ~10\u201315% of $8.08: trust the real-world baseline as comparator.\n- Diverges 15\u201330% consistently: re-anchor at this Lab baseline.\n- Diverges >50% or non-determ.: stop, diagnose apparatus before variant.\n\nCodex pinned to aff280e \u2014 the parent of the cartograph commission's\nsealed commit (607b572). This is the codex state the original planner\nsaw. Brief is the verbatim writ body extracted from w-mojmj0rc.\n\npatronRole is set to 'patron' (matching vibers config) so the\nreader-analyst uses sage-primer-attended (the role X018 will inject the\nsurface map into). patron-anima runs but, per the running-trials.md\nrecipe, decision-review fast-paths when the primer pre-fills selected\nvalues (which the cartograph's decisions did in the original session).\n\nwaitForRigTerminal=true (the spec-only mandate writ never seals so\nwrit-based wait would time out; rig-based wait polls the spider rig\nto its terminal RigStatus) with a 30-min cap. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY flows\nthrough to the test guild's daemon via process.env inheritance.\n",
